  ('cfb1883c-bf70-410d-afe2-8273467ea099', 'GENERAL', 31, '{"itemType":"CLAUSE","clause_number":"6.3","clause_title":"Operations and Methods of Execution","clause_text":"(a) The Contractor shall comply with all applicable rules, regulations and procedures relating to safety matters in its access arrangements and Site operations. (b) Without prejudice to any other obligations under the Contract the Contractor shall take full responsibility for the supervision, adequacy, stability and safety of all Site operations, of all methods of execution and of all the Works, irrespective of any approval or consent by the Supervision Consultant or the Project Manager. (c) When working on the Site, any area for the time being occupied by the Employer or any area designated by the Project Manager the Contractor shall strictly observe and perform each and every provision of the Employer''s and the Project Manager''s rules, regulations and procedures relating to safety matters for the time being in force. (d) The Contractor shall take all necessary steps to protect the environment (both on and off the Site) and to avoid damage and nuisance to people and property resulting from pollution, noise and other results of its operations. This shall include the Contractor providing temporary roadways, footways, guards and fences which may be rendered necessary, by reason of the carrying out of the Works, for the use and protection of the public and of owners and occupiers of adjacent land. The Contractor shall ensure that emissions, surface discharges and effluent from the Contractor''s activities shall not exceed the values indicated in the Contract and shall not exceed the values prescribed by the applicable laws. (ii) the access to and use and occupation of all roads and footpaths, irrespective of whether they are public or in the possession of the Employer or of others. The Contractor shall indemnify and hold the Employer harmless against and from all damages, losses and expenses (includi