  ('cfb1883c-bf70-410d-afe2-8273467ea099', 'GENERAL', 44, '{"itemType":"CLAUSE","clause_number":"9.1","clause_title":"Information and Inspection","clause_text":"Insofar as the Employer may have made available to the Contractor prior to the Contractor submitting its Tender any information concerning the Site and its surroundings or conditions applicable thereto the Employer accepts no liability for the sufficiency or accuracy of such information and the Contractor shall be responsible for its own interpretation thereof. For the avoidance or removal of doubt, the Contractor hereby accepts the entire risk as to the condition of the Site and all data produced in respect thereof and hereby agrees that it will not submit any claim nor commence any proceedings in connection therewith. The Contractor shall be deemed to have inspected and examined the Site and its surroundings and information available in connection therewith and to have satisfied itself prior to submitting its Tender as to: (a) the form and nature of the Site and its surroundings, including the sub-surface, hydrological, hydrographic and climatic conditions thereof; Accordingly, the Contract Sum and the rates and prices in the Bills of Quantities shall be deemed to take account of all such matters and the Contractor shall not be entitled to make any claim in relation thereto whether for variation, extension of time or otherwise.","general_condition":"Insofar as the Employer may have made available to the Contractor prior to the Contractor submitting its Tender any information concerning the Site and its surroundings or conditions applicable thereto the Employer accepts no liability for the sufficiency or accuracy of such information and the Contractor shall be responsible for its own interpretation thereof. For the avoidance or removal of doubt, the Contractor hereby accepts the entire risk as to the condition of the Site and all data produced in respect thereof and hereby agrees that it will not submit any